other_tests.findings: Evaluation of intra-abdominal organs and structures are somewhat limited without the administration of IV contrast. A 1.4 cm hypodense lesion is seen at the liver dome, slightly increased compared to prior study, and likely represents a cyst. The appendix is dilated and measures up to 9 mm with surrounding fat stranding consistent with acute appendicitis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Slightly increased size of liver lesion compared to prior study.
